abstract: The detention of Prince Alwaleed and other top royals have introduced questions among investors over potential instability in the kingdom.
snippet: The detention of Prince Alwaleed and other top royals have introduced questions among investors over potential instability in the kingdom.
lead_paragraph: Good Monday morning. Andrew has thoughts on the detention of Prince Alwaleed of Saudi Arabia over the weekend, especially after interviewing the billionaire less than two weeks ago. And weâ€™re looking at the fallout from the Paradise Papers leaks.

abstract: The mayor said in an interview that he has focused on clear numerical goals and timelines, stressing outcomes rather than the process.
snippet: The mayor said in an interview that he has focused on clear numerical goals and timelines, stressing outcomes rather than the process.
lead_paragraph: The government of New York City is enormous, with more than 295,000 full-time employees and an annual budget of $85 billion, presenting a host of challenges for any manager. The New York Times asked Mayor Bill de Blasio, the Democrat who is seeking a second term, about his approach to management, the experiences that inform his decisions as a manager and his vision for New York City over the next four years.
